annotationA: Probable Ufm1-specific protease 1; Thiol protease which recognizes and hydrolyzes the peptide bond at the C-terminal Gly of UFM1, a ubiquitin-like modifier protein bound to a number of target proteins
annotationB: Ubiquitin-fold modifier-conjugating enzyme 1; E2-like enzyme which forms an intermediate with UFM1 via a thioester linkage
